# Security Standards and Best Practices

## Authentication & Authorization
- Use secure password hashing (bcrypt)
- Implement proper session management
- Use CSRF protection
- Implement rate limiting
- Use secure HTTP headers
- Use JWT tokens with proper expiration
- Implement multi-factor authentication where possible

## Data Protection
- Use HTTPS everywhere
- Sanitize all user inputs
- Use parameterized queries
- Encrypt sensitive data at rest
- Implement proper access controls
- Use AWS KMS for encryption
- Enable EBS volume encryption
- Use S3 server-side encryption
- Enable RDS encryption

## Input Validation
- Validate all user inputs
- Use whitelist validation where possible
- Sanitize HTML content
- Prevent SQL injection attacks
- Prevent XSS attacks
- Use proper content type validation

## Dependencies
- Keep dependencies up to date
- Use dependency scanning tools (Trivy, Bandit)
- Pin dependency versions
- Review third-party code
- Use Snyk or similar tools for vulnerability scanning
- Regularly audit dependencies

## API Security
- Implement proper authentication for all endpoints
- Use HTTPS for all API calls
- Implement rate limiting
- Use proper HTTP status codes
- Validate request payloads
- Implement proper error handling without information leakage

## Database Security
- Use least privilege database users
- Encrypt database connections
- Use parameterized queries
- Implement proper backup encryption
- Use database connection pooling
- Implement proper logging and monitoring

## Infrastructure Security
- Use security groups and network ACLs
- Implement proper IAM policies
- Use VPC for network isolation
- Enable CloudTrail logging
- Use AWS Config for compliance monitoring
- Implement proper key rotation

## Monitoring and Logging
- Log all security events
- Monitor for suspicious activity
- Use centralized logging
- Implement proper log retention
- Monitor access patterns
- Set up security alerts

## Compliance
- Follow OWASP Top 10 guidelines
- Implement CIS benchmarks
- Follow AWS Well-Architected Framework
- Implement GDPR compliance measures
- Regular security assessments
- Penetration testing

## Incident Response
- Have incident response plan
- Document security procedures
- Regular security training
- Incident reporting procedures
- Post-incident reviews
- Security metrics tracking
